  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nWhile working with foundry, if we copy the below code from ReadMe, it will say file not found\r\n```\r\nimport {ERC721} from \"@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol\";\r\n```\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nSince the file is not found, it may be confusing for some developers.\r\nSo, can we give the  remappings example in Readme? \r\n\r\nNote: Only while working with Foundry\r\n```\r\nremappings = [\"@openzeppelin/=lib/openzeppelin-contracts/\"]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen, \r\n```\r\nimport {ERC721} from \"@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol\";\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf this will help few devs, then I would like to make this changes.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
